devdoc.details: ensure usingAugur is set to false upon local testing and true on kovan or mainnet

_collectRent(uint256).details: also calculates and updates how long the current user has held the token for

collectRentAllTokens().details: makes it easy for me to call whenever I want to keep people paying their rent

complete().details: users pull dai into their account. Replaces previous push vesion which required looping over unbounded mapping.

exit(uint256).details: do not need to be the current owner

liveDepositAbleToWithdraw(uint256).return: how much the current owner has deposited

rentOwed(uint256).details: called in collectRent function, and various other view functions

step1checkMarketsResolved().details: they are split into two sections due to the presence of step1BemergencyExit and step1CcircuitBreakercan be called by anyone can be called multiple times, but only once after markets have indeed resolvedthe two arguments passed are for testing only

step2sellCompleteSetsAndPayAndrew().details: gets funds back from Augur, gets the available funds for distribution and pays me my 1%can be called by anyone, but only once

userDepositAbleToWithdraw(uint256).return: how much the current user has deposited (note: user not owner)

withdrawDeposit(uint256,uint256).details: do not need to be the current owner

withdrawDepositAfterResolution().details: the other withdraw deposit functions are locked when markets have resolved so must use this one... which can only be called if markets have resolved. This function is also different in that it does ... not attempt to collect rent or transfer ownership to a previous owner

devdoc.title: Harber

_collectRent(uint256).notice: collects rent for a specific token

changePrice(uint256,uint256).notice: increase the price of an existing rental

collectRentAllTokens().notice: /////////// ORDINARY COURSE OF BUSINESS FUNCTIONS //////////////collects rent for all tokens

complete().notice: the final function of the competition resolution process. Pays out winnings, or returns funds, as necessary

depositDai(uint256,uint256).notice: add new dai deposit to an existing rental

step1BemergencyExit().notice: emergency function in case the augur markets never resolve for whatever reasonreturns all funds to all userscan only be called 6 months after augur markets should have ended

step1CcircuitBreaker().notice: Same as above, except that only I can call it, and I can call it wheneverto be clear, this only allows me to return all funds. I can not set a winner.

step1checkMarketsResolved().notice: /////////// MARKET RESOLUTION FUNCTIONS ////////////// the first of two functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competitionwinnings can be paid out (or funds returned) only when these two steps are completedthis function checks whether the Augur markets have resolved, and if yes, whether they resolved correct or not

step2sellCompleteSetsAndPayAndrew().notice: the second of the two functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competition

withdrawDepositAfterResolution().notice: withdraw full deposit after markets have resolved
